Day #12 ITIL Practices.

Practice: People who follow processes are called practices.

ISMS Practices: it ensures this service gets delivered with proper information Security in place. include all service chain activity performed.

Customer data or user data is controlled and secure with no lapses to perform risk management
to find out what information is at risk.

Create information Security Policies for customers, Users & Employees in your organization.
you define information security policies for all these stack holders.
You will define what access controls are there and provisioned. what all access control you put in place what all access control has been granted to stack holders.

Information Security aims to protect the data (information).
Three Critical information security factors are available that is confidentiality, integrity, and availability.
Confidentiality: This means the right person has the right access at the right time.
Integrity: This means that the trueness of your data is supposed to be not tempered.
Availability: this means data is available when a customer wants it. 

Based on the CIA Approach policies should differ as per stack holder.

For example: What access your employee is entirely different, Which access does your vendor that's why CIA is different for different stack holders.

The benefits of implementing this practice, you avoid information security incidents in your organization, you can perform audits in your organization, 
and all configuration items. that is why this information is important.
