Day #13 Relationship Management Practice.

To establish relationships with your stakeholders at the strategic level and tactical levels.
You need relationship management, this practice bridges customer requirements and needs, customer priority has been identified, BR manager understands customer needs, 
understands the customer wants service from me as the customer, what are the outcomes the customer looking for and already achieved.

The Main objective of Business Relationship management is to understand customers' expectations. both customer priority and satisfaction are taken into consideration.

Any complaints customers have are being looked into.

There are three key relationships with business stakeholders.

(1) Strategic: Long-term business relationship.
(2) Tactical: Operational Relationship (Achievement of the output).

There are different Roles involved in customer Relationship Management.

Key Account Manager.
Business Relationship Manager.
Relationship Manager.

Most of the time these people on the customer site and being onsite understand the customer requirements, and they understand all unsaid expectations.

They understand requirements within the environment and accordingly, they convey the requirement to the service delivery manager, 
who is responsible for delivering customer requirements. it very important to have this practice.
