Day #14 Supplier Management Practice.

Supplier is an external organization, with whom we need to work to provide customer services.
The source material came from a supplier.

Objective: To maintain a healthy relationship with all suppliers.

You have strategies, 
What is sourcing strategy,
What needs to outsource, 
What needs to insource, 
How many suppliers do you need, 
What type of supplier do you need, 
How much work should be outsourced, 
Who is the best supplier for you, and why? 
how many categories of suppliers do you have, 

Need to set and Define Policies.
Categorized the supplier. 
You should have a vendor database.
Strategic Supplier.
Tactical Supplier.
Evaluate the Supplier.
You should monitor supplier performance.
Renewal of Contract with supplier.
Supplier performance measurement we should check whether vendors are working as per contract agreement or not. Need to check SLAs and Parameters.

Multiple types of supplier relationships also exist.

In-Sourcing: The company's employees give support same company Users.
Out Sourcing: Outside suppliers give support to your company employees.
Co-Sourcing: Mix of external and internal Resources giving support.
Multi-sourcing: Multiple Vendors working on big contracts for a single customer.
Single/Partnerships sourcing: Two Companies merge and work on a particular project.

Supplier Managers need to keep the Supplier Database with their contracts.
